value.0: Calibast is the fiery azer who once led your stalwart party of five. He is largely immune to fire-based attacks, and is powerfully built.

Calibast's helm is a family heirloom, a rememberance of his long dead parents. Though he does not speak of them much, his occassional stretches of melancholy are often due to his reminicing about his childhood. Obviously the scavengers could not wrest the helm off of his flaming head.
Having been banished from her home plane, Jaboli became one of your companions, forsaking the natural socerous ways of her people in favor of more *rational* wizardly pursuits.

Jaboli's well-worn boots may not draw a lot of attention for those looking for a fashion statement, but they are very useful. Jaboli has had this same set of boots for many years and will not willingly give them up.

The fire that destroyed Kaidala's home left her scarred physically and emotionally. Though she has never fully accepted her new life, her abilities as a druid are often remarkable. Kaidala has a kind and gentle spirit, and her fearlessness can make her quite formidable in battle.

This outfit is magically made from the leaves and bark of a tree from Kaidala's home. It was a gift from the forest and Kaidala treasures it. She will not willingly part with this last rememberance of her former life.
Trip is one of your erstwhile companions. As a wererat, he has the ability to bite and cause disease. He is also a rogue and has the uncanny ability to find odd and well-hidden treasures.
This is Trip's magic talisman, a dirty, old rat's skull hung on a leather thong. Trip often chews on the skull and believes it brings him luck. He will not part with the charm.
